ownedComment.body: In the next release, there will be a link to available services too.
Asset can have only one controller and location. A user can have only one location. No duplicities.

The keywords depend on the development team. Example suggestions are: user (u), created (c), tag (t), location (l), body (b), specification (s)*, state (f). The user can use long version of short (in brackets).
*Specification refers to type/category/producer of an asset.
If the user scroll to the bottom, show older changes.
Invoice code from the accounting application.
Connections include AND, OR and brackets.
But not the items – no users/assets should be removed.
Relationship can be <, <=, =, >=, >. The value is what the keyword should be like. An example is name="Excel" or created>=12.7.2018.
Yes it is possible to link items while viewing completely different item.
Separately for each type of item – locations, assets, users. Possible options – Yes, Set manually, No, Cancel
Does not remove the item nor target, just the connection between the instances.
And services in the next release.
